    43→        "content": "     1→[\n     2→  {\n     3→    \"role\": \"user\",\n     4→    \"content\": [\n     5→      {\n     6→        \"tool_use_id\": \"toolu_015V4B24RWLoypf8eLVMJnEm\",\n     7→        \"type\": \"tool_result\",\n     8→        \"content\": \"     1→---\\n     2→task: m-implement-complete-healing-branch-types\\n     3→branch: feature/implement-complete-healing-branch-types\\n     4→status: completed\\n     5→created: 2025-09-05\\n     6→started: 2025-09-05\\n     7→modules: [internal/cli/transflow, roadmap/transflow, tests]\\n     8→---\\n     9→\\n    10→# Complete Healing Branch Types Implementation\\n    11→\\n    12→## Problem/Goal\\n    13→The transflow healing infrastructure has production Nomad job submission working, but the healing branch types need completion. Currently, human-step branches are just placeholders, and comprehensive testing coverage is needed for all branch types (llm-exec, orw-gen, human-step). Additionally, the roadmap needs to be updated to reflect completed tasks and follow TDD principles from @AGENTS.md.\\n    14→\\n    15→## Success Criteria\\n    16→- [x] Implement complete human-step branch handler with Git-based manual intervention workflow\\n    17→- [x] Ensure llm-exec branch type is fully functional with MCP tool integration\\n    18→- [x] Verify orw-gen branch type works with OpenRewrite recipe generation and application\\n    19→- [x] Add comprehensive test coverage for all three healing branch types\\n    20→- [x] Update roadmap/transflow/MVP.md to mark completed tasks and current status\\n    21→- [x] Follow TDD framework from @AGENTS.md: RED (failing tests) → GREEN (minimal code) → REFACTOR (VPS testing)\\n    22→- [x] Deploy to VPS for integration testing following mandatory update protocol\\n    23→- [x] Update FEATURES.md and CHANGELOG.md as needed\\n    24→\\n    25→## Context Manifest\\n    26→\\n    27→### How This Currently Works: Transflow Self-Healing Architecture\\n    28→\\n    29→The transflow healing infrastructure is a sophisticated multi-phase workflow system that automatically recovers from build failures using parallel healing strategies. When a transflow execution encounters a build failure, it triggers a three-phase healing process: **planner → fanout → reducer**.\\n    30→\\n    31→#### Phase 1: Planner Job Analysis\\n    32→\\n    33→When a build fails during the normal transflow workflow (clone → branch → recipes → commit → **build failure**), the `attemptHealing` method in `runner.go` is called with the build error message. The healing process begins by creating a `TransflowHealingSummary` to track the entire healing attempt.\\n    34→\\n    35→The system first submits a **planner job** via `JobSubmissionHelper.SubmitPlannerJob()`. This planner is a Nomad batch job that analyzes the build error context and generates healing options. The planner job runs in a Docker container with the LangGraph planner model, receiving:\\n    36→- Build error details and context\\n    37→- Repository metadata and state\\n    38→- Knowledge base snapshots (future enhancement)\\n    39→\\n    40→The planner writes a `plan.json` artifact containing an array of healing options. Each option specifies a different healing strategy with its own type and confidence score.\\n    41→\\n    42→#### Phase 2: Fanout Orchestration (Parallel Branch Execution)\\n    43→\\n    44→Once the planner completes, the system converts the planner options into `BranchSpec` structures and submits them to the `FanoutOrchestrator`. This orchestrator implements a **first-success-wins** parallel execution model with configurable parallelism limits.\\n    45→\\n    46→The fanout orchestrator launches multiple healing \\\"branches\\\" simultaneously:\\n    47→- **llm-exec**: LLM-powered code generation that analyzes the error and generates a patch\\n    48→- **orw-gen**: OpenRewrite recipe generation that suggests and applies automated refactoring recipes  \\n    49→- **human-step**: Manual intervention workflow that creates Git branches/MRs for human review\\n    50→\\n    51→Each branch executes as an independent Nomad job with its own resource allocation and timeout. The orchestrator uses Go channels and context cancellation to coordinate the parallel execution. When the first branch succeeds, it cancels all remaining branches to prevent resource waste.\\n    52→\\n    53→#### Phase 3: Reducer Decision Making\\n    54→\\n    55→After branch execution completes (either with a winner or all failures), the system submits a **reducer job** via `JobSubmissionHelper.SubmitReducerJob()`. The reducer analyzes all branch results and the winning solution to determine the next action.\\n    56→\\n    57→The reducer typically returns `{\\\"action\\\": \\\"stop\\\", \\\"notes\\\": \\\"healing succeeded\\\"}` when a branch successfully fixes the build, allowing the main transflow workflow to continue with the healed changes.\\n    58→\\n    59→#### Branch Type Implementations (Current State)\\n    60→\\n    61→**llm-exec branches** (`executeLLMExecBranch` in `fanout_orchestrator.go`):\\n    62→- Renders LLM execution assets using `RenderLLMExecAssets()` \\n    63→- Substitutes environment variables in the HCL template (MODEL, TOOLS_JSON, LIMITS_JSON, RUN_ID)\\n    64→- Submits as Nomad job using `orchestration.SubmitAndWaitTerminal()`\\n    65→- Expects the job to produce a `diff.patch` artifact in the output directory\\n    66→- Validates success by checking for the diff.patch file existence\\n    67→\\n    68→**orw-gen branches** (`executeORWGenBranch`):\\n    69→- Renders OpenRewrite application assets using `RenderORWApplyAssets()`\\n    70→- Extracts recipe configuration from branch inputs (class, coords, timeout)\\n    71→- Performs recipe-specific HCL variable substitution (RECIPE_CLASS, RECIPE_COORDS, RECIPE_TIMEOUT)\\n    72→- Submits as Nomad job and waits for completion\\n    73→- Validates success by checking for generated diff.patch artifact\\n    74→\\n    75→**human-step branches** (`executeHumanStepBranch`):\\n    76→- Currently returns immediate failure with \\\"not yet implemented\\\" message\\n    77→- Intended to create Git branches/MRs for manual intervention\\n    78→- Should poll for manual commits and validate build success after human changes\\n    79→\\n    80→### For New Feature Implementation: Completing the Missing Pieces\\n    81→\\n    82→Since we're implementing complete healing branch types with comprehensive test coverage, several critical integration points need completion:\\n    83→\\n    84→#### Human-Step Branch Implementation Requirements\\n    85→\\n    86→The current human-step implementation is a placeholder that immediately fails. The complete implementation needs to:\\n    87→\\n    88→1. **Git Branch Creation**: Create a dedicated Git branch for human intervention, separate from the main workflow branch\\n    89→2. **Issue/MR Creation**: Use the existing `GitProvider` interface to create GitLab merge requests with detailed error context\\n    90→3. **Polling Mechanism**: Implement a polling loop that checks for manual commits on the human intervention branch\\n    91→4. **Build Validation**: After detecting manual changes, re-run the build check to verify the fix\\n    92→5. **Timeout Handling**: Respect branch-level timeouts and gracefully fail if human intervention doesn't occur\\n    93→\\n    94→The human-step workflow should integrate with the existing `r.gitProvider` (GitLab integration) and `r.buildChecker` interfaces already available in the `TransflowRunner`.\\n    95→\\n    96→#### Test Coverage Completion\\n    97→\\n    98→The existing test infrastructure in `job_submission_test.go` and `self_healing_test.go` uses a `MockJobSubmitter` pattern that simulates job execution. The missing test coverage needs to address:\\n    99→\\n   100→1. **Branch Type Validation**: Tests for each branch type (llm-exec, orw-gen, human-step) with both success and failure scenarios\\n   101→2. **Timeout Handling**: Tests that verify proper timeout behavior and context cancellation\\n   102→3. **Error Recovery**: Tests that validate error handling when branches fail at different stages\\n   103→4. **Integration Testing**: End-to-end tests that combine planner → fanout → reducer workflows\\n   104→\\n   105→The test infrastructure already provides `MockJobSubmitter` with configurable `JobResults` mapping and error injection capabilities.\\n   106→\\n   107→#### Production Job Submission Integration\\n   108→\\n   109→The healing workflow integrates with the existing Nomad job submission infrastructure through the `orchestration.SubmitAndWaitTerminal()` function. The production flow:\\n   110→\\n   111→1. **Asset Rendering**: Uses `RenderLLMExecAssets()`, `RenderORWApplyAssets()` to prepare HCL job templates\\n   112→2. **Variable Substitution**: Performs environment variable substitution in HCL templates using `substituteHCLTemplate()`\\n   113→3. **Job Submission**: Calls `orchestration.SubmitAndWaitTerminal()` with rendered HCL paths and timeout values\\n   114→4. **Artifact Collection**: Reads job output artifacts (diff.patch files) from expected output directories\\n   115→5. **Result Processing**: Parses artifacts and determines branch success/failure\\n   116→\\n   117→The existing HCL templates in `roadmap/transflow/jobs/` define the Nomad job specifications with placeholder variables that get substituted at runtime.\\n   118→\\n   119→### Technical Reference Details\\n   120→\\n   121→#### Component Interfaces & Signatures\\n   122→\\n   123→```go\\n   124→// Main healing orchestration entry point\\n   125→func (r *TransflowRunner) attemptHealing(ctx context.Context, repoPath string, buildError string) (*TransflowHealingSummary, error)\\n   126→\\n   127→// Job submission interfaces\\n   128→type JobSubmissionHelper interface {\\n   129→    SubmitPlannerJob(ctx context.Context, config *TransflowConfig, buildError string, workspace string) (*PlanResult, error)\\n   130→    SubmitReducerJob(ctx context.Context, planID string, results []BranchResult, winner *BranchResult, workspace string) (*NextAction, error)\\n   131→}\\n   132→\\n   133→// Fanout orchestration\\n   134→type FanoutOrchestrator interface {\\n   135→    RunHealingFanout(ctx context.Context, runCtx interface{}, branches []BranchSpec, maxParallel int) (BranchResult, []BranchResult, error)\\n   136→}\\n   137→\\n   138→// Branch execution methods\\n   139→func (o *fanoutOrchestrator) executeLLMExecBranch(ctx context.Context, branch BranchSpec, result BranchResult) BranchResult\\n   140→func (o *fanoutOrchestrator) executeORWGenBranch(ctx context.Context, branch BranchSpec, result BranchResult) BranchResult\\n   141→func (o *fanoutOrchestrator) executeHumanStepBranch(ctx context.Context, branch BranchSpec, result BranchResult) BranchResult\\n   142→```\\n   143→\\n   144→#### Data Structures\\n   145→\\n   146→```go\\n   147→// Healing summary tracking\\n   148→type TransflowHealingSummary struct {\\n   149→    Enabled       bool                       `json:\\\"enabled\\\"`\\n   150→    AttemptsCount int                        `json:\\\"attempts_count\\\"`\\n   151→    MaxRetries    int                        `json:\\\"max_retries\\\"`\\n   152→    Attempts      []*TransflowHealingAttempt `json:\\\"attempts\\\"`\\n   153→    FinalSuccess  bool                       `json:\\\"final_success\\\"`\\n   154→    PlanID        string                     `json:\\\"plan_id,omitempty\\\"`\\n   155→    Winner        *BranchResult              `json:\\\"winner,omitempty\\\"`\\n   156→    AllResults    []BranchResult             `json:\\\"all_results,omitempty\\\"`\\n   157→}\\n   158→\\n   159→// Branch specifications and results\\n   160→type BranchSpec struct {\\n   161→    ID     string                 `json:\\\"id\\\"`\\n   162→    Type   string                 `json:\\\"type\\\"`   // \\\"llm-exec\\\", \\\"orw-gen\\\", \\\"human-step\\\"\\n   163→    Inputs map[string]interface{} `json:\\\"inputs\\\"`\\n   164→}\\n   165→\\n   166→type BranchResult struct {\\n   167→    ID         string        `json:\\\"id\\\"`\\n   168→    Status     string        `json:\\\"status\\\"`     // \\\"completed\\\", \\\"failed\\\", \\\"timeout\\\", \\\"cancelled\\\"\\n   169→    JobID      string        `json:\\\"job_id\\\"`\\n   170→    Notes      string        `json:\\\"notes\\\"`\\n   171→    StartedAt  time.Time     `json:\\\"started_at\\\"`\\n   172→    FinishedAt time.Time     `json:\\\"finished_at\\\"`\\n   173→    Duration   time.Duration `json:\\\"duration\\\"`\\n   174→}\\n   175→```\\n   176→\\n   177→#### Configuration Requirements\\n   178→\\n   179→```yaml\\n   180→# transflow.yaml self-healing configuration\\n   181→self_heal:\\n   182→  enabled: true\\n   183→  max_retries: 2      # Maximum healing attempts (1-5)\\n   184→  cooldown: 30s       # Optional cooldown between attempts\\n   185→```\\n   186→\\n   187→Environment variables for healing jobs:\\n   188→- `TRANSFLOW_MODEL`: LLM model for healing (default: gpt-4o-mini@2024-08-06)\\n   189→- `TRANSFLOW_TOOLS`: MCP tools configuration JSON\\n   190→- `TRANSFLOW_LIMITS`: Execution limits configuration JSON\\n   191→\\n   192→#### File Locations\\n   193→\\n   194→- **Main Implementation**: \\n   195→  - `internal/cli/transflow/runner.go` - Main healing orchestration in `attemptHealing()`\\n   196→  - `internal/cli/transflow/fanout_orchestrator.go` - Branch execution logic (needs human-step completion)\\n   197→  - `internal/cli/transflow/job_submission.go` - Nomad job submission helpers\\n   198→\\n   199→- **Test Files**:\\n   200→  - `internal/cli/transflow/self_healing_test.go` - Healing workflow tests (needs branch-specific coverage)\\n   201→  - `internal/cli/transflow/job_submission_test.go` - Job submission tests (needs human-step tests)\\n   202→  - `internal/cli/transflow/integration_test.go` - End-to-end integration tests\\n   203→\\n   204→- **Nomad Job Templates**:\\n   205→  - `roadmap/transflow/jobs/llm_exec.hcl` - LLM execution job template\\n   206→  - `roadmap/transflow/jobs/orw_apply.hcl` - OpenRewrite application job template\\n   207→  - Need to create: `roadmap/transflow/jobs/human_step.hcl` (if job-based approach is used)\\n   208→\\n   209→- **Documentation Updates**:\\n   210→  - `roadmap/transflow/MVP.md` - Update implementation status from \\\"Partially Implemented\\\" to \\\"Fully Implemented\\\"\\n   211→  - `FEATURES.md` - Document completed healing branch types\\n   212→  - `CHANGELOG.md` - Record implementation completion\\n   213→\\n   214→## User Notes\\n   215→- Follow @AGENTS.md TDD framework strictly - write failing tests first, minimal implementation, then VPS refactor phase\\n   216→- Human-step branch should involve creating Git branches/MRs and polling for manual commits\\n   217→- All branch types should have proper error handling and timeout management\\n   218→- Tests should cover both success and failure scenarios for each branch type\\n   219→- Integration with existing Nomad job submission infrastructure is already complete\\n   220→\\n   221→## Work Log\\n   222→\\n   223→### 2025-09-05\\n   224→\\n   225→#### Completed - TDD Implementation Cycle (RED → GREEN → REFACTOR)\\n   226→\\n   227→**Phase 1: RED Phase - Failing Test Implementation**\\n   228→- Implemented comprehensive failing tests for human-step branch implementation (TestHumanStepBranchCurrentBehavior)\\n   229→- Created failing tests for llm-exec branch validation including HCL asset rendering, environment variable substitution, Nomad job submission, and artifact validation\\n   230→- Added failing tests for orw-gen branch validation covering recipe configuration extraction and template processing\\n   231→- Implemented timeout and error handling test scenarios for all branch types\\n   232→- Added integration tests for fanout orchestration with first-success-wins semantics\\n   233→\\n   234→**Phase 2: GREEN Phase - Minimal Implementation**\\n   235→- Implemented complete human-step branch handler (executeHumanStepBranch) with Git-based manual intervention workflow\\n   236→  - MR creation via GitProvider interface with detailed error context\\n   237→  - Commit polling mechanism with configurable timeouts and build validation\\n   238→  - Build checker integration using common.DeployConfig structure\\n   239→  - Proper error handling for missing dependencies (GitProvider, BuildChecker)\\n   240→- Verified and enhanced llm-exec branch functionality with production Nomad integration\\n   241→  - HCL template rendering via RenderLLMExecAssets method\\n   242→  - Environment variable substitution for TRANSFLOW_MODEL, TRANSFLOW_TOOLS, TRANSFLOW_LIMITS, RUN_ID\\n   243→  - Production job submission using orchestration.SubmitAndWaitTerminal()\\n   244→  - diff.patch artifact collection and validation\\n   245→- Verified and enhanced orw-gen branch functionality\\n   246→  - Recipe configuration extraction from branch inputs (class, coords, timeout)\\n   247→  - Template variable substitution (RECIPE_CLASS, RECIPE_COORDS, RECIPE_TIMEOUT)\\n   248→  - OpenRewrite job execution and artifact processing\\n   249→- Extended ProductionBranchRunner interface with human-step support methods\\n   250→  - Added GetGitProvider(), GetBuildChecker(), GetWorkspaceDir() methods\\n   251→  - Integration with TransflowRunner infrastructure for production deployments\\n   252→\\n   253→**Phase 3: Production Integration and Documentation**\\n   254→- Enhanced fanout orchestration system with context cancellation and resource cleanup\\n   255→  - Semaphore-based parallelism control with configurable maximum concurrent branches\\n   256→  - Automatic cancellation of remaining branches when first branch succeeds\\n   257→  - Comprehensive timeout handling with proper status tracking and duration recording\\n   258→- Updated roadmap/transflow/MVP.md to mark healing branch types as \\\"Fully Implemented\\\"\\n   259→  - Moved LangGraph healing branch types from \\\"Partially Implemented\\\" to complete status\\n   260→  - Updated implementation details to reflect all three branch types (human-step, llm-exec, orw-gen)\\n   261→  - Updated fanout orchestration status to reflect production-ready capabilities\\n   262→- Updated CHANGELOG.md with comprehensive entry documenting all healing branch implementation work\\n   263→  - Added detailed feature descriptions for all three branch types\\n   264→  - Documented production job submission integration with HCL template processing\\n   265→  - Included fanout orchestration system with first-success-wins parallel execution\\n   266→  - Listed comprehensive test coverage achievements and TDD implementation approach\\n   267→\\n   268→#### Decisions\\n   269→- Chose Git-based manual intervention approach for human-step branches over job-based polling\\n   270→  - Enables direct human interaction through familiar GitLab MR interface\\n   271→  - Leverages existing GitProvider infrastructure and build validation systems\\n   272→  - Provides better visibility and collaboration workflow for manual fixes\\n   273→- Implemented first-success-wins fanout orchestration with context cancellation\\n   274→  - Prevents resource waste by cancelling remaining branches when one succeeds\\n   275→  - Uses semaphore-based parallelism control for configurable concurrency limits\\n   276→  - Provides proper timeout handling and error propagation throughout the system\\n   277→- Extended ProductionBranchRunner interface to support human-step branch requirements\\n   278→  - Maintains clean separation between test and production implementations\\n   279→  - Enables dependency injection for GitProvider and BuildChecker in production mode\\n   280→  - Supports comprehensive test coverage with mock implementations\\n   281→\\n   282→#### Technical Implementations\\n   283→- **File Changes**: \\n   284→  - `internal/cli/transflow/fanout_orchestrato